{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|2Co|6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","chapter":6,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v11","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:6:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":6,"verse":1,"text":"Working together with him, we also appeal to you, “Don’t receive the grace of God in vain.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:6:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":6,"verse":2,"text":"For he says: See, now is the acceptable time; now is the day of salvation!","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:6:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":6,"verse":3,"text":"We are not giving anyone an occasion for offense, so that the ministry will not be blamed.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:6:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":6,"verse":4,"text":"Instead, as God’s ministers, we commend ourselves in everything: by great endurance, by afflictions, by hardships, by difficulties,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:6:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":6,"verse":5,"text":"by beatings, by imprisonments, by riots, by labors, by sleepless nights, by times of hunger,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:6:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":6,"verse":6,"text":"by purity, by knowledge, by patience, by kindness, by the Holy Spirit, by sincere love,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:6:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":6,"verse":7,"text":"by the word of truth, by the power of God; through weapons of righteousness for the right hand and the left,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:6:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":6,"verse":8,"text":"through glory and dishonor, through slander and good report; regarded as deceivers, yet true;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:6:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":6,"verse":9,"text":"as unknown, yet recognized; as dying, yet see —we live; as being disciplined, yet not killed;","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:6:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":6,"verse":10,"text":"as grieving, yet always rejoicing; as poor, yet enriching many; as having nothing, yet possessing everything.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:6:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":6,"verse":11,"text":"We have spoken openly to you, Corinthians; our heart has been opened wide.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:6:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":6,"verse":12,"text":"We are not withholding our affection from you, but you are withholding yours from us.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:6:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":6,"verse":13,"text":"I speak as to my children; as a proper response, open your heart to us.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:6:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":6,"verse":14,"text":"Do not be yoked together with those who do not believe. For what partnership is there between righteousness and lawlessness? Or what fellowship does light have with darkness?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:6:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":6,"verse":15,"text":"What agreement does Christ have with Belial? Or what does a believer have in common with an unbeliever?","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:6:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":6,"verse":16,"text":"And what agreement does the temple of God have with idols? For we are the temple of the living God, as God said:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:6:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":6,"verse":17,"text":"Therefore, come out from among them","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:6:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","bookOrder":46,"chapter":6,"verse":18,"text":"And I will be a Father to you,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Co","chapter":6,"paragraphStarts":[1,3,14,17,18],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":3,"text":"The Character of Paul’s Ministry"},{"beforeVerse":14,"text":"Separation to God"}],"poetryBlocks":[],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:6:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Working together with him, we also appeal to you, “Don’t receive the grace of God in vain.” "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Co:6:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"For he says:"},{"kind":"text","text":" See, now is the acceptable time; now is the day of salvation! "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 49:8","book":"Isa","chapter":49,"verse":8,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Is 55:6","book":"Isa","chapter":55,"verse":6,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Lk 4:19","book":"Luk","chapter":4,"verse":19,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Heb 3:13","book":"Heb","chapter":3,"verse":13,"letter":"d"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Is 49:8","book":"Isa","ch